ioStudio SyncContent Magento Extension (CE)
===========================================

This extension will allow you to sync content and databases with a dev, staging,
and production servers.

Requirements
------------

  * Magento CE >= 1.6.1.0
    NOTE: Other versions may work, but this extension was developed on this version

Installation
------------

Install into the apps/community directory. The file structure of this plugin should
match where everything needs to go, so you could just do a copy/paste.

Configuration
-------------

To start the setup, you will need to log into the admin section of magento.

    System > Configuration
    IOSTUDIO > SyncContent Options

*Url* This is the URL where you site is, when syncing the database, this is used
  so magento doesn't do anything crazy

*Host* This is the IP address or domain name for that server.

*Username* is what the username is for that server

*Port* is used to configure the port in case you have ssh enabled on a nonstandard port

*Directory* is the path to where the store is installed on that server

*Rsync Options* This is an advanced setting and is used whenever you are syncing
  content to or syncing content from that server

Usage
-----

To use the scripts, you must be on the command line.

shell/iostudio_synccontent.php
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

Allows you to sync files and folders from on server to another

Examples:

You are on your dev machine and you want to pull down files and folders from the
production server. The command you would use is:

    php shell/iostudio_synccontent.php --sync-from production

The same command would be used if you are logged into the staging or test servers,
in a nut shell, you are pulling down files and folders from production to the
machine you are currently on.


shell/iostudio_syncdatabase.php
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

Allows you to sync the database from one server to another

Examples:

You are on you development machine and you want to pull down the database from
the production server, you would use this command:

    php shell/iostudio_syncdatabase.php --sync-from production

This command will make a backup of your database before it syncs the production
database to your machine